-- Hong Kong Home Sales Drop to Lowest in 14 Months, Land Registry Estimates
-- Nipa Piboontanasawat
-- 2010-07-05T07:49:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-05/hong-kong-s-home-sales-decline-to-lowest-level-in-14-months-4-2-billion.html

          
          
             Hong Kong’s home sales fell to HK$33
billion in June, the lowest level in 14 months, from HK$42.8
billion in May, data from the Land Registry showed.  
 By volume, the number of residential units changing hands
declined to 9,130 in June from 11,014 in May, according to the
Land Registry’s website.  
          
          


  


        